inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_user_id
inputs.info: The user's email address or 'me' for the authenticated user.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_subject
inputs.info: Subject of the event. Example: 'Team Meeting'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_body
inputs.info: Body content of the event. Can be plain text or HTML.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_is_html
inputs.info: Set to True if the body content should be interpreted as HTML.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_start_datetime
inputs.info: Start date/time (ISO 8601). Example: '2025-01-03T10:00:00Z'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_end_datetime
inputs.info: End date/time (ISO 8601). Example: '2025-01-03T11:00:00Z'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_time_zone
inputs.info: Time zone (e.g., 'UTC' or 'America/Los_Angeles').

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_is_online_meeting
inputs.info: Set to True to make this an online meeting and generate a Teams URL.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_online_meeting_provider
inputs.info: The online meeting service provider. Currently only supports 'teamsForBusiness'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_attendees_info
inputs.info: A list of attendee information. Only email is required for each attendee., Example: [{ 'email': 'team@example.com', 'name': 'Team', 'type': 'required' }, { 'email': 'other@example.com', 'type': 'optional' }, { 'email': 'other2@example.com' }]

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_location
inputs.info: Location of the event (e.g., 'Conference Room').

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_show_as
inputs.info: Status of the event: 'free', 'tentative', 'busy', or 'oof'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_CALENDAR_CREATE_EVENT_categories
inputs.info: List of categories associated with the event comma separated.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_GET_EVENT_user_id
inputs.info: The user's email address or 'me' for the authenticated user.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_GET_EVENT_event_id
inputs.info: The ID of the calendar event to retrieve.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_user_id
inputs.info: The target user's email address or 'me' for the authenticated user. For delegated access scenarios, this should be the email of the shared mailbox or delegated user.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_top
inputs.info: The maximum number of messages to return per request. Must be a positive integer between 1 and 1000.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_skip
inputs.info: The number of messages to skip before starting to collect results. Use for paginated responses.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_is_read
inputs.info: Filter messages by read status. If set to False, only unread messages will be returned.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_importance
inputs.info: Filter messages by importance. For example, 'high', 'normal', or 'low'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_subject
inputs.info: Filter messages by subject (exact match).

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_received_date_time_gt
inputs.info: Filter messages with a receivedDateTime greater than the specified value. Example: '2023-01-01T00:00:00Z'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_subject_startswith
inputs.info: Filter messages where the subject starts with the specified string.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_subject_endswith
inputs.info: Filter messages where the subject ends with the specified string.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_subject_contains
inputs.info: Filter messages where the subject contains the specified substring.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_received_date_time_ge
inputs.info: Filter messages with a receivedDateTime greater than or equal to the specified value.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_received_date_time_lt
inputs.info: Filter messages with a receivedDateTime less than the specified value.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_received_date_time_le
inputs.info: Filter messages with a receivedDateTime less than or equal to the specified value.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_from_address
inputs.info: Filter messages by the sender's email address. Uses equality check on from/emailAddress/address.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_has_attachments
inputs.info: Filter messages by whether they have attachments.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_body_preview_contains
inputs.info: Filter messages where the bodyPreview contains the specified substring.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_sent_date_time_gt
inputs.info: Filter messages with a sentDateTime greater than the specified value.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_sent_date_time_lt
inputs.info: Filter messages with a sentDateTime less than the specified value.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_categories
inputs.info: Filter messages by categories. Matches if the message contains any of the specified categories.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_select
inputs.info: A list of properties to include in the response comma separated. Common properties: 'subject', 'from', 'toRecipients', 'receivedDateTime'.

inputs.name: OUTLOOK_OUTLOOK_LIST_MESSAGES_orderby
inputs.info: Specify properties to sort results by. For example, 'receivedDateTime desc' for newest messages first.
